data.title: History and Traditions
data.text:
Established by the United States Constitution, the Supreme Court began to take shape with the passage of the Judiciary Act of 1789 and has enjoyed a rich history since its first assembly in 1790. The Supreme Court is deeply tied to its traditions: Of the federal governmentâ€™s three branches, the Court bears the closest resemblance to its original form.
